item.title: Who cares about this?
item.dc:creator: @boriz boriz
item.description:
@boriz wrote:

WOW I am one of the luckiest guys ever.

I was working on it and decided to boot up and try out a mouse that was on the shelf for a few years. I forgot that it malfunctioned a while back. Plugged that fucker into my USB and POW huge spark.

I almost cried but after a restart it looks like the usb hub is still working!

I’m thinking about how linux will handle the fingerprint reader and if I need it in the first place. Installing ubuntu now, just to see if it’ll boot correctly through usb.

Wireless mouse working flawlessly. Video of WIP in action coming up in a few days if I’m not lazy.

Stupid mouse didn’t come with an on/off switch so I had to open it up and solder one in into the usb holder. Really tough but I got it working flawlessly.

item.title: Who cares about this?
item.dc:creator: @boriz boriz
item.description:
@boriz wrote:

Finally gonna give you guys an update, because you convinced me:

NEW PICS OMFG
http://img365.imageshack.us/img365/5481/laptopexplanation.jpg

(close up)
http://img18.imageshack.us/img18/3497/dscf0898.jpg

Sorry that I was too lazy to focus the camera.

Now an explanation to the 500GB HDD:
My hard drive controller died for some unknown reason (no hard drives detected in bios). I was in no mood to fix it (pretty sure that’s impossible anyways). I wanted to upgrade my hard drive anyways so I put a 500GB SATA HD with a separate controller and power supply.

Now, there was A LOT of work done with this. You have no idea. I have spent many nights brainstorming how I’ll be able to fit in so much stuff into the case.

Also, you may be asking, “why the hell not just get a new, better laptop?”
I will tell you:
Where is the fun in that? I am broke, I have electronics skills, I have patience and infinite time. You won’t get such features in a laptop as COAX input, TV tuner (maybe) and 7 USB ports… wireless mouse without receiver, 2" speakers, light up touchpad etc.
Making something yourself is one of the most rewarding things you can do. I can be proud of my project when I finish with it.

Leave me some comments please.
